issue.title: Replace usage of `cgi` gem for Ruby 3.5
issue.body:
In Ruby 3.5 most of the cgi gem will be removed.
Only the various escape/unescape methods will be retained by default.

But, it is a bit cumbersome to find a uniform solution that works on all supported rubies, so use the same functionality provided via `erb` instead.

I've confirmed this works down to Ruby 2.0

https://bugs.ruby-lang.org/issues/21258

Korbit conducts comprehensive, context-based PR code reviews. Let Korbit AI review your PRs first; it will find and help you fix bugs fast, then submit the PR for team review/approval—and Korbit will help there, too.

Korbit increases productivity, improves code quality, and upskills developers.

- **Issue Detection and Fixes:** Detects issues in your code and shows you how to fix them, fast.
- **PR Description and Summary:** Korbit generates a PR Description and a Summary of its review, giving everyone clear context into the purpose of the PR.
- **Interactive PR Bot:** Interactive bot to answer questions, provide recommendations, and examples to guide you through the tough ones.
- **Supports All Languages:** Korbit works on all common programming languages.
- **Safe and Secure:** Korbit enforces a zero retention, zero access policy. None of your code or data is ever seen, retained, or used to train any models, ever.

## Benefits

- **Increased Productivity:** Up to a 3x productivity increase for developers and a 70% reduction in PR review time.
- **Improved Code Quality:** Finds and resolves issues that may have been missed.
- **Developer Upskilling:** Provides explanations, recommendations, and interactive feedback to continuously improve skills.
- **Seamless Workflow Integration:** No changes to your PR workflow.
- **Immediate Value:** Install, select a repository, and Korbit will automatically go to work and you’ll see the results in your next PRs.

Working on an open-source project? Korbit Pro is free for all open-source repositories!

issue.title: A working example of FreeIPA in Kubernetes 1.26
issue.body:
Hi,

After searching for current examples of working Kubernetes manifests that I could use to deploy FreeIPA in my home lab I ended up having to piece one together from a number of posts and repos. I thought it would be good for me to document what I learned.

I'm [deploying FreeIPA as a StatefulSet](https://github.com/iPenguin/bare-metal-kubernetes/blob/master/roles/freeipa/templates/freeipa-statefulset.yaml.j2) with a MetalLB [LoadBalancer in front of it](https://metallb.universe.tf/](https://github.com/iPenguin/bare-metal-kubernetes/blob/master/roles/freeipa/templates/freeipa-lb.yaml.j2)).

The biggest thing I found missing in all the examples I saw was the need for a `startupProbe`. This block prevents the pod from being killed during the long startup on initial install (15+ minutes) without adversely impacting pod restarts.

```
  startupProbe:
    httpGet:
      path: /
      port: 80
    failureThreshold: 35
    periodSeconds: 30
``` 

I hope someone else finds this helpful.
-Brian

comment.body:
Hello,
First of all, thank you so much for your great and active community!

I'm writing in reference to the manifest that user @iPenguin  kindly shared earlier.
 I tried deploying the manifest myself, and I encountered a problem during restart named service in install phase — it fails unless I set privileged: true.

When I do set privileged: true, everything works well and the installation completes successfully. However, after a pod restart, the hostname changes, and the FreeIPA service fails to start correctly.

I checked the logs of the named service, and it fails with a systemd start service timeout, which seems to be the root cause

Here are a few additional details about my environment:

    Kubernetes version: 1.29.5

    OS: Rocky Linux 9.4

    SELinux: Disabled

I’ve tried the following to troubleshoot:

    Used different base images like Rocky and CentOS.

    Set the IPA_SERVER_IP environment variable explicitly in the relevant container.
    
    Remove And Modify  securityContext Section

Unfortunately, none of these changes resolved the issue.

I'm wondering if there is any document or recommended approach for handling this scenario — especially how  run the pod successfully without privileged mode.

Below is my current manifest: 

```yaml

apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: freeipa
spec:
  selector:
    app: freeipa
  clusterIP: 10.233.5.115
  ports:
  - name: http
    port: 80
    targetPort: 80
  - name: https
    port: 443
    targetPort: 443
  - name: dns-tcp
    port: 53
    protocol: TCP
    targetPort: 53
  - name: dns-udp
    port: 53
    protocol: UDP
    targetPort: 53
  - name: kerberos-tcp
    port: 88
    protocol: TCP
    targetPort: 88
  - name: kerberos-udp
    port: 88
    protocol: UDP
    targetPort: 88
  - name: kpasswd-tcp
    port: 464
    protocol: TCP
    targetPort: 464
  - name: kpasswd-udp
    port: 464
    protocol: UDP
    targetPort: 464
  - name: ldap
    port: 389
    protocol: TCP
    targetPort: 389
  - name: ldaps
    port: 636
    protocol: TCP
    targetPort: 636
---
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: StatefulSet
metadata:
  name: freeipa
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: freeipa
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: freeipa
    spec:
      containers:
        - name: freeipa-container
          image: freeipa/freeipa-server:rocky-9 # almalinux , centos  
          resources:
            requests:
              memory: "5Gi"
              cpu: "2"
            limits:
              memory: "5Gi"
              cpu: "2"
          imagePullPolicy: Always
          env:
            - name: IPA_SERVER_HOSTNAME
              value: freeipa.freetest.freeipame
            - name: IPA_SERVER_INSTALL_OPTS
              value: --unattended --realm=FREETEST.FREEIPAME --domain freetest.freeipame --ip-address=10.233.5.115 -p P@ssw0rd!@# -a P@ssw0rd!@# --no-forwarders --ssh-trust-dns --setup-dns --no-ntp 
          securityContext:
            capabilities:
              add: 
                - SYS_TIME
                - NET_BIND_SERVICE
            seccompProfile:
              type: Unconfined
          volumeMounts:
            - name: freeipa-server-data
              mountPath: /data
            - name: cgroups
              mountPath: /sys/fs/cgroup
            - name: run
              mountPath: /run
            - name: tmp
              mountPath: /tmp
            - mountPath: /dev/shm
              name: dshm
      volumes:
        - name: cgroups
          hostPath:
            path: /sys/fs/cgroup
        - name: run
          emptyDir:
            medium: Memory
        - name: tmp
          emptyDir:
            medium: Memory
        - name: dshm
          emptyDir:
            medium: Memory
            sizeLimit: 5Gi
        - name: freeipa-server-data
          persistentVolumeClaim:
            claimName: freeipa-server-data

```
Thanks in advance for your support and guidance
